    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-20T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-20T05:00:00-05:00" n="111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.60F31/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wright</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Praha</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-20T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 20, 1935—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 20—9:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Your 9, March 13, 5 p.m. In interview on the 16th instant Foreign Office
                    denied discrimination against any commodity or country, requested data on
                    specific cases, expressed desire to await publication of Belgian agreement
                    before making further observations; and upon being informed yesterday of my
                    receipt of your telegram 11, March 18, 7 p.m., states that similar word has been
                    received from Legation, Washington and that matter is under consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wright</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
